# TypeScript

Use TypeScript (with types) in:

- `src/lib/` — `site.ts`, `schema.ts`, `work.ts`, etc.
- `src/actions/` — Astro Actions
- `src/content/config.ts` — collection schemas (Zod)
- `src/pages/api/**/*.ts` — API routes

**Not** in Astro component `<script>` blocks — those stay plain JS (see `astro.mdc`).

## Content collections (`content/config.ts`)

| Collection | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| `work` | Case study MDX frontmatter |
| `services` | Service page copy + FAQs, schema fields |
| `service-locations` | Geo/service landing pages |

Extend Zod schemas when adding frontmatter fields; keep MDX under `src/content/<collection>/`.

## Actions (`actions/index.ts`)

- Contact `send`: Zod input, Resend email, `ActionError` on failure.
- Form: `ContactForm.astro` → `method="post"` `action={actions.send}`.
- **Env** (Vercel): `RESEND_API_KEY`, `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL`, `RESEND_TO_EMAIL`.

## Lib helpers

- **`url(path)`** in `site.ts` — absolute URLs for schema/sitemap.
- **`schema.ts` / `work.ts`** — page titles, descriptions, JSON-LD builders; reuse instead of duplicating strings in pages.

## API routes

- Follow `src/pages/api/work/[slug].json.ts` for JSON endpoints.
- Validate inputs; return appropriate HTTP status codes.
